<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-13T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-13T15:00:00-05:00" n="436" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/61: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-13T16:00:00-04:00">March 13,
                                    1942—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>52. Your 71, March 12, 3 p.m.<note n="15" xml:id="d436fn15">Not
                                printed.</note> For McBride from Villard. Text of agreement is
                            satisfactory as far as we are concerned but War Department has not yet
                            given its approval. Except for possible minor modifications we do not
                            believe that any change will be necessary. Official reply will be sent
                            as soon as possible.</p>
                        <p>Please repeat last paragraph of Legation’s 68, March 11, 9 a.m., which
                            appears incomplete. Our telegram regarding Lend-Lease aid should more
                            than answer credit question.</p>
                        <p>Congratulations on excellent work so far. [Villard.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>